{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/control\/scale"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"title":"scale","roleHeading":"Instance Property","fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"scale","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"Vector2","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:10SwiftGodot7Vector2V"}],"externalID":"s:10SwiftGodot7ControlC5scaleAA7Vector2Vvp","modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}],"role":"symbol","symbolKind":"property"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The node’s scale, relative to its "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"size"},{"type":"text","text":". Change this property to scale the node around its "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Control\/pivotOffset","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". The Control’s "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Control\/tooltipText"},{"text":" will also scale according to this value.","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Control"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"final","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"scale"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Vector2","text":"Vector2","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:10SwiftGodot7Vector2V"},{"text":" { ","kind":"text"},{"text":"get","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"set"},{"text":" }","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","level":2},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This property is mainly intended to be used for animation purposes. To support multiple resolutions in your project, use an appropriate viewport stretch mode as described in the [url=$DOCS_URL\/tutorials\/rendering\/multiple_resolutions.html]documentation[\/url] instead of scaling Controls individually."}]}],"name":"Note","style":"note","type":"aside"},{"name":"Note","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/FontFile\/oversampling"},{"type":"text","text":" does "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"not","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" take "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Control"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Control\/scale","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" into account. This means that scaling up\/down will cause bitmap fonts and rasterized (non-MSDF) dynamic fonts to appear blurry or pixelated. To ensure text remains crisp regardless of scale, you can enable MSDF font rendering by enabling "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ProjectSettings\/gui\/theme\/defaultFontMultichannelSignedDistanceField"},{"text":" (applies to the default project font only), or enabling ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Multichannel Signed Distance Field","type":"text"}]},{"text":" in the import options of a DynamicFont for custom fonts. On system fonts, ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/SystemFont\/multichannelSignedDistanceField","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" can be enabled in the inspector."}]}],"style":"note"},{"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If the Control node is a child of a ",